      • University

        public University(java.lang.String name,
                  java.lang.String state,
                  java.lang.String location,
                  java.lang.String control,
                  int numberOfStudents,
                  double percentFemale,
                  double satVerbal,
                  double satMath,
                  double expenses,
                  double percentFinancialAid,
                  int numberOfApplicants,
                  double percentAdmitted,
                  double percentEnrolled,
                  int academicScale,
                  int socialScale,
                  int qualityOfLifeScale,
                  java.lang.String emphasis)
           throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        A constructor that creates a University object with all of the requirements
        Parameters:
        name - of the university
        state - in which university is located
        type - of location university is located (urban, rural, suburban, etc.)
        subjects - that are emphasized at the university
        control - of the university (public or private)
        number - of students at the university
        percent - of female students at the university
        average - SAT Verbal score for enrolled students
        average - SAT Math score for enrolled students
        anual - expenses or tuition to attend university
        percent - of financial aid given to students at university
        number - of students that applied to university
        percent - of students admitted to university
        percent - of students that decide to enroll at university
        academic - scale indicating the academic scale at university (1-5)
        social - scale indicating social life at university (1-5)
        quality - of life scale indicating the quality of life at university (1-5)
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentsException - if the academicScale parameter is not between 1 and 5
        IllegalArgumentsException - if the socialScale parameter is not between 1 and 5
        IllegalArgumentsException - if the qualityOfLifeScale parameter is not between 1 and 5
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
